{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the object that is being returned already exists)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using this function on the return value of the userâ€™s callback allows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"alway receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that has been converted to a full reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" instance. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_take_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindingref\/takeref()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/takeRef()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"takeRef()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject10BindingRefV","extendedModule":"GLibObject","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"role":"collection","title":"GLibObject","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"ObjectRef","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ObjectRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ObjectRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindingref\/objectprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingRef/takeRef()":{"role":"symbol","title":"takeRef()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef\/takeRef()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindingref\/takeref()"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"BindingRef","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBinding"},{"type":"text","text":" is the representation of a binding between a property on a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" instance (or source) and another property on another "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance (or target)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingRef","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindingref"}}}